## Key Design Decisions

  - Dev: localStorage + X-Auth-Token (localhost fix)
  - Production: httpOnly cookie (Vercel proxy forwards it)
  - Backend accepts both Cookie and X-Auth-Token headers everywhere
  - Frontend middleware.ts only checks cookie existence (not decryption)
  - Full auth validation always happens at backend /api/auth/me

## Rollback Plan

  If production fails:
  1. Revert to previous commit
  2. Vercel: redeploy from git
  3. Render: redeploy from git
  4. DATABASE_URL → sqlite:// ... (only if PostgreSQL migration failed)
